From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: detect FAT corruption + auto-reformat via fs_mkfs

After patches 0036-0040, fs_open still returns -ENOENT on /SD:/a01.txt
on every boot after the first successful one. mount_sd_card succeeds
but file ops fail — the FAT structure is corrupt at a level that
fs_unlink can't recover.

This patch adds a "FAT health check" right after mount: try opening a
test file. If that fails, fs_unmount + fs_mkfs (reformat) + remount.
The FAT comes back clean and subsequent file ops work.

Targeted/non-destructive: a healthy FAT skips the format. Only a
detected-corrupt FAT triggers the reformat path. Requires
CONFIG_FILE_SYSTEM_MKFS=y and CONFIG_FS_FATFS_MKFS=y in the build
(added to spisd-fixup.conf).
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
index ad07db1..9107c6d 100644
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
@@ -86,10 +86,29 @@ int mount_sd_card(void)
      * half-committed FAT entries (fs_close -EIO during normal writes
      * leaves the file unrecoverable on next boot). */
     int unlink_ret = fs_unlink("/SD:/a01.txt");
     LOG_INF("boot: fs_unlink(/SD:/a01.txt) = %d", unlink_ret);
 
+    /* Patch 0041: detect FAT corruption + reformat via fs_mkfs. */
+    {
+        struct fs_file_t test_f;
+        fs_file_t_init(&test_f);
+        int test_ret = fs_open(&test_f, "/SD:/.fmttest", FS_O_WRITE | FS_O_CREATE);
+        if (test_ret == 0) {
+            fs_close(&test_f);
+            fs_unlink("/SD:/.fmttest");
+            LOG_INF("boot: FAT health check OK");
+        } else {
+            LOG_WRN("boot: FAT health test fs_open=%d, reformatting...", test_ret);
+            fs_unmount(&mount_point);
+            int mkfs_ret = fs_mkfs(FS_FATFS, (uintptr_t)"SD", NULL, 0);
+            LOG_INF("boot: fs_mkfs = %d", mkfs_ret);
+            int rem_ret = fs_mount(&mount_point);
+            LOG_INF("boot: re-fs_mount = %d", rem_ret);
+        }
+    }
+
     res = fs_mkdir("/SD:/audio");
 
     if (res == FR_OK) {
         LOG_INF("audio directory created successfully");
         initialize_audio_file(1);
